<doc id="12233" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=12233" title="Myron Cope, Pittsburgh Steelers color commentator, retires after a 35 year career">
<h1>Myron Cope, Pittsburgh Steelers color commentator, retires after a 35 year career</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Myron%20Cope%2C%20Pittsburgh%20Steelers%20color%20commentator%2C%20retires%20after%20a%2035%20year%20career&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="w%3AMyron%20Cope"&gt;Myron Cope&lt;/a&gt;, a locally famous sports announcer for the &lt;a href="w%3APittsburgh%20Steelers"&gt;Pittsburgh Steelers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href="w%3ANational%20Football%20League"&gt;National Football League&lt;/a&gt; team, has announced his retirement from the booth, effective immediately. Cope had a 35 year career announcing Steelers games with his familiar scratchy voice, often punctuated with unique &lt;a href="w%3AYiddish"&gt;Yiddish&lt;/a&gt; expressions, such as "Feh" and "Yoi", which brought delight to fans.

