<doc id="13026" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=13026" title="Unanimous U.S. Supreme Court rules against file swapping companies/Brief">
<h1>Unanimous U.S. Supreme Court rules against file swapping companies/Brief</h1>
<h2>&lt;a href="Unanimous%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20rules%20against%20file%20swapping%20companies"&gt;Unanimous U.S. Supreme Court rules against file swapping companies&lt;/a&gt;</h2>

Writing for a unanimous &lt;a href="w%3ASupreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States"&gt;U.S. Supreme Court&lt;/a&gt;, Justice &lt;a href="w%3ADavid%20Souter"&gt;David Souter's&lt;/a&gt; decision mad file sharing companies who provide tools for users to violate copyright law are liable for those infringements. The decision directly affects plaintiffs &lt;a href="w%3AGrokster"&gt;Grokster&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AStreamCast"&gt;StreamCast&lt;/a&gt;, but the cases have been remanded to a lower court for final adjudication.


