<doc id="13284" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=13284" title="Bodies found at crash site of US helicopter in Afghanistan/Brief">
<h1>Bodies found at crash site of US helicopter in Afghanistan/Brief</h1>
<h2>&lt;a href="Bodies%20found%20at%20crash%20site%20of%20US%20helicopter%20in%20Afghanistan"&gt;Bodies found at crash site of US helicopter in Afghanistan&lt;/a&gt;</h2>
Thirteen bodies have been found at the site where a US helicopter crashed yesterday in Afghanistan.
Seven more soldiers are unaccounted for - including soldiers who were fighting on the ground at the time of the crash. "It's a search and recovery operation in a tactical environment, which means we have to ensure security throughout," U.S. military spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Jerry O'Hara said.


