<doc id="13460" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=13460" title="Soul musician Luther Vandross dies at age 54">
<h1>Soul musician Luther Vandross dies at age 54</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Soul%20musician%20Luther%20Vandross%20dies%20at%20age%2054&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Musician &lt;a href="w%3ALuther%20Vandross"&gt;Luther Vandross&lt;/a&gt; died at 1:47 pm Eastern time Friday, at a hospital in Edison, New Jersey, likely from complications related to a 2003 stroke.

He was the winner of numerous &lt;a href="w%3AGrammy%20Award"&gt;Grammy Award&lt;/a&gt;s.

<h2>Sources</h2>
<ul>
BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//abclocal.go.com/wabc/features/entertainment/wabc_070105_vandrossobit.html"&gt;Musician Luther Vandross Dies At 54&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AWABC"&gt;WABC&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, July 1, 2005

</ul>
<ul>
