<doc id="13469" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=13469" title="Explosion in Russia kills 10: authorities suspect Chechen involvement">
<h1>Explosion in Russia kills 10: authorities suspect Chechen involvement</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Explosion%20in%20Russia%20kills%2010%3A%20authorities%20suspect%20Chechen%20involvement&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

The &lt;a href="w%3AItar-Tass"&gt;Itar-Tass&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3Anews%20agency"&gt;news agency&lt;/a&gt; reports that an explosion in the southern &lt;a href="Russia"&gt;Russia&lt;/a&gt;n town of &lt;a href="Makhachkala"&gt;Makhachkala&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Dagestan"&gt;Dagestan&lt;/a&gt;, has killed 10 soldiers and wounded 20 others on Friday. Two bombs were set off in a &lt;a href="w%3Abath%20house"&gt;bath house&lt;/a&gt; at 2:15 pm local time as the soldiers were passing outside, according to an official of the Russian Interior Ministry. Dagestan borders &lt;a href="Chechnya"&gt;Chechnya&lt;/a&gt;, which has a long history of uprisings against Russian rule. The current insurrection started at the time of the breakup of the Soviet Union in 1990.

