<doc id="13476" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=13476" title="Microsoft to pay IBM US $775 million in Antitrust settlement">
<h1>Microsoft to pay IBM US $775 million in Antitrust settlement</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Microsoft%20to%20pay%20IBM%20US%20%24775%20million%20in%20Antitrust%20settlement&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

According to a report in the &lt;a href="w%3ANew%20York%20Times"&gt;New York Times&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3AMicrosoft"&gt;Microsoft&lt;/a&gt; will pay &lt;a href="w%3AIBM"&gt;IBM&lt;/a&gt; Corporation US $775 million to settle &lt;a href="w%3Aantitrust"&gt;antitrust&lt;/a&gt; claims which resulted from the &lt;a href="w%3AFederal%20government%20of%20the%20United%20States"&gt;U.S. government&lt;/a&gt;'s antitrust lawsuit against the &lt;a href="w%3Asoftware"&gt;software&lt;/a&gt; manufacturer. The issues dealt with Microsoft's actions in reducing the value of IBM's &lt;a href="w%3AOS/2"&gt;OS/2&lt;/a&gt; operating system, which competed with Microsoft's &lt;a href="w%3AWindows"&gt;Windows&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AOperating%20System"&gt;Operating System&lt;/a&gt;. This settlement with IBM follows several other settlements of hundreds of millions of dollars each with &lt;a href="w%3ASun%20Microsystems"&gt;Sun Microsystems&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3AAmerica%20Online"&gt;America Online&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3AGateway"&gt;Gateway&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3ANovell"&gt;Novell&lt;/a&gt;. Microsoft also has a lawsuit pending against it that was filed by &lt;a href="w%3AReal%20Networks"&gt;Real Networks&lt;/a&gt;, as well as an appeal of a US $600 million fine imposed by &lt;a href="w%3AEurope"&gt;Europe&lt;/a&gt;an antitrust regulators.

